The paper proposes a method for learning the graph structure and parameters of graph convolutional networks, which is a problem commonly studied in the machine learning community. The paper also mentions conducting experiments to analyze the behavior of the proposed method, which suggests a focus on empirical evaluation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
